  "prompt": "Do car manufacturers produce new models every year?",
  "response": "Car manufacturers typically release new models or updates to existing models on a regular basis, but not every manufacturer introduces completely new models every year. Instead, many automakers might follow a cycle that includes:\n\n1. **Annual Updates**: Minor changes or updates to existing models, such as new features, technology updates, or design tweaks.\n\n2. **Facelifts**: A significant refresh of an existing model that can occur every few years, involving changes in design, features, and sometimes performance enhancements.\n\n3. **New Generations**: A completely new version of a model that may be introduced every five to seven years, depending on the model and the manufacturer's strategy.\n\n4. **All-New Models**: Some brands may introduce all-new models at various intervals, depending on market trends and production schedules.\n\n5. **Special Editions**: Manufacturers might also offer special editions of existing models, which can create a sense of novelty without being entirely new models.\n\nWhile large manufacturers tend to have annual product cycles that yield new or updated vehicles, smaller companies or brands may not release new models every year. Additionally, the introduction of electric vehicles and changes in consumer preferences can influence product development timelines.",
